.Op Fl Fl env-file Ar file
.Cm cancel
.Op Fl Fl project Ar name
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a tool for running multi-jail environments on
.Xr appjail 1
using a simple YAML specification. A
.Xr director-spec 5
file is used to define how one or more jails that make up your application are configured. Once you have a
.Xr director-spec 5
file, you can create and start your application with a single command:
.Sy appjail-director up Ns "."
.Pp
The configuration files are loaded in the following order:
.Pa %%PREFIX%%/etc/director.ini Ns , Pa ~/.config/director/director.ini Ns , from the environment variable
.Ev DIRECTOR_CONFIG
and from the
.Fl Fl config
option. Only the first two are loaded if they exist, otherwise they are ignored. When specifying the configuration file from the environment variable or from the command-line option, you must be sure that these files exist, otherwise an error will be displayed.
.Pp
An environment file specified by
.Fl Fl env-file
is loaded if it exists, otherwise it is ignored. This file is very useful for when you need to put some secrets or some dynamic values in your
.Xr director-spec 5
file but they should not be in it and probably not in a repository either.
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width xxx
.It Cm up Oo Fl Fl json Oc Oo Fl Fl overwrite Oc Oo Fl Fl quiet Oc Oo Fl Fl file Ar file Oc Oo Fl Fl project Ar name Oc
Reads a
.Xr director-spec 5
file.                                                                                                                                       
.Pp                                                                                                                                                           
Any access to a file or directory specified in the
.Xr director-spec 5
file is relative to it, not to the current directory in which
.Nm
is running.
.Pp
When a
.Xr director-spec 5
file specified by
.Fl Fl file
is read,
.Nm
will perform some checks to verify if it needs to create or recreate a service.
.Pp
The checks that
.Nm
performs are:
.Sy overwrite Ns , Sy differing Ns , Sy failed Ns , Sy mtime No and Sy  differing_options Ns "."
.Sy overwrite
will recreate the service if the
.Fl Fl overwrite
option is specified.
.Sy differing
will recreate the service if it differs from the old file that is copied each time the
.Cm up
command is executed.
.Sy failed
will recreate the service if it has previously failed in some way
.Po e.g. creating or starting it Pc Ns "."
.Sy mtime
will recreate the service if the
.Xr appjail-makejail 5
modification time differs from the old one, but if
.Sy ignore_mtime
is specified this does not apply.
.Sy differing_options
will recreate the service if the global options change from the previous one, but if
.Sy reset_options
is
.Sy true Ns , it is ignored. Of course, if a service does not exist,
.Nm
will create it. A service is also created if the project is new
.Po does not exist previously Pc Ns "."
.Pp
By default, when a project is not specified using the
.Fl Fl project
option,
.Nm
tries to read the
.Ev DIRECTOR_PROJECT
environment variable and, if it is not set, a random name is chosen.
.Pp
When removing a service
.Po specifically, the jail Pc Ns , the
.Sy remove_force
and
.Sy remove_recursive
options specified from the configuration file determine the behavior of this action.
.Bl -tag -width xx
.It Fl j Ns , No Fl Fl json
Output in JSON format.
.It Fl Fl overwrite
Recreate all services, even when it is not necessary.
.It Fl q Ns , No Fl Fl quiet
Quiet mode: suppress normal output.
.It Fl f Ar file Ns , No Fl Fl file Ar file
Specify an alternate
.Xr director-spec 5
file.
.Pp
Default:
.Em appjail-director.yml
.It Fl p Ar name Ns , No Fl Fl project Ar name
Specify an alternate name. If none is specified, a random name is used.
.El
.It Cm down Oo Fl Fl ignore-failed Oc Oo Fl Fl ignore-services Oc Oo Fl Fl json Oc Oo Fl Fl quiet Oc Oo Fl Fl destroy Oc Oo Fl Fl project Ar name Oc
Stops the project and if the
.Fl Fl destroy
flag is used, it will be destroyed. Destroy implies stopping and destroying all
the jails in that project and removing the project completely. Logs are not
removed, you should remove them manually using system commands when you don't
need them.
.Pp
The project name is obtained from the command-line option and, if not set, from
the
.Ev DIRECTOR_PROJECT
environment variable.
.Bl -tag -width xx
.It Fl Fl ignore-failed
Ignore services that are not destroyed.
.It Fl Fl ignore-services
Ignore services.
.It Fl j Ns , No Fl Fl json
Output in JSON format.
.It Fl q Ns , No Fl Fl quiet
Quiet mode: suppress normal output.
.It Fl d Ns , No Fl Fl destroy
Destroy the project after stopping and destroying each service.
.It Fl p Ar name Ns , No Fl Fl project Ar name
Project name.
.El
.It Cm ls Oo Fl Fl state Ar state Oc
Lists projects.
.Pp
In addition to simply displaying the project name, the current status of the
project is shown symbolically on the left side as follows:
.Sy +
.Po Sy DONE Pc Ns ,
.Sy -
.Po Sy FAILED Pc Ns ,
.Sy ! No
.Po Sy UNFINISHED Pc Ns ,
.Sy x
.Po Sy DESTROYING Pc Ns ,
.Sy ?
.Po Sy UNKNOWN Pc Ns "."
.Bl -tag -width xx
.It Fl s Ar state Ns , No Fl Fl state Ar state
Project status.
.Pp
Default:
.Em done Ns , Em failed Ns , Em unfinished No and Em destroying
.El
.It Cm info Oo Fl Fl project Ar name Oc
Show information about a project.
.Pp
In addition to displaying the services, the current status of each service is
shown symbolically on the left side as follows:
.Sy +
.Po Sy RUNNING Pc Ns ,
.Sy -
.Po Sy STOPPED Pc Ns ,
.Sy ! No
.Po Sy FAILED Pc Ns "."
In addition for
.Sy ! Ns , the status code will be displayed.
.Pp
The project name is obtained from the command-line option and, if not set, from the
.Ev DIRECTOR_PROJECT
environment variable.
.It Cm describe Oo Fl Fl project Ar name Oc
Like
.Cm info
but in JSON format.
.Bl -tag -width xx
.It Fl p Ar name Ns , No Fl Fl project Ar name
Project name.
.El
.It Cm check Oo Fl Fl project Ar name Oc
Returns
.Sy 0
if a project exists or non-zero if it does not exist.
.Bl -tag -width xx
.It Fl p Ar name Ns , No Fl Fl project Ar name
Project name.
.El
.It Cm cancel Oo Fl Fl project Ar name Oc
Sends a
.Sy SIGTERM
signal to a running project.
.Pp
For this to succeed, the project state must be
.Sy UNFINISHED
and the registered parent PID must be the same as the parent PID of the
currently running process.
.Bl -tag -width xx
.It Fl p Ar name Ns , No Fl Fl project Ar name
Project name.
.El
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width xxx
.It DIRECTOR_CONFIG
Configuration file.
.It DIRECTOR_PROJECT
Project name.
.El
